        <mxCell id="SSQ6IqG1F6KoJnQz6ak4-82" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="The Data Access Layer is repsonsible for receiving data outside of the whole CHMS system and preparing it for the rest of the sytem.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;The external signal generator can send data in different ways, such as through TCP, WebSocket, or log files. To keep the system flexible, all these input methods are handled through a shared &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;324&quot; data-end=&quot;338&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;DataListener&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; interface. The classes &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;362&quot; data-end=&quot;379&quot; style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Helvetica&quot;&gt;TCPDataListener&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;381&quot; data-end=&quot;404&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;WebSocketDataListener&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;, and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;410&quot; data-end=&quot;428&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;FileDataListener&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; all implement this interface, so they all provide a common way to collect raw data, even though the source is different.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;After the raw data is received, it is passed to the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;608&quot; data-end=&quot;620&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;DataParser&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. The parser converts the raw input, such as JSON or CSV text, into&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;713&quot; data-end=&quot;728&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;PatientRecord&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. This makes sure the data has the same structure before it enters the main system.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;The &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;817&quot; data-end=&quot;836&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;DataSourceAdapter&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; connects these parts together. It uses a listener to collect raw data, sends it to the parser, and then passes the parsed &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;959&quot; data-end=&quot;974&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;PatientRecord&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt; to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;code data-start=&quot;978&quot; data-end=&quot;991&quot; style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;DataStorage&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: Helvetica; background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;. This separation is important because the storage and rest of the system do not need to know whether the data came from TCP, WebSocket, or a file. This makes the design easier to maintain and extend later.&lt;/span&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="450" x="20" y="-290" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
